<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 28 at 10:25AM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...RAIN CHANGING TO SNOW WILL LEAD TO POOR TRAVEL CONDITIONS...
Rain has begun to change over to snow across central Connecticut
which will lead to poor travel conditions through around noon time
today. Minor snowfall accumulations of upwards of once inch are
possible. Motorists are urged to drive with extra caution over the
next couple of hours as untreated roads may become snow/slush
covered and slippery.</description>
